        <h2>Life Forms and Geological Features</h2>
        <p>The Paleozoic Era, lasting from approximately 541 to 252 million years ago, saw the development of early life forms, including fish, amphibians, and the first land plants. It ended with the largest mass extinction event in Earth’s history.</p>
